-- 
Aral Wants to Lift Gas Price Level in Germany, Die Welt Reports

-- B y   R a g n h i l d   K j e t l a n d
-- 
2011-08-28T14:19:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-28/aral-wants-to-lift-gas-price-level-in-germany-die-welt-reports.html
Aral,  Germany ’s largest gas station
franchise, wants to achieve a higher gas price level at its
2,500 gas stations,  Die Welt  reported, citing confidential Aral
documents that is obtained.  Aral is planning a new model for provisions, under which
the owners of the gas station receive a higher commission if
they sell gas and diesel for a higher price over a prolonged
period, according to the e-mailed preview of an article that
will appear in tomorrow’s edition. Currently the gas station
operators are paid according to volumes sold, Die Welt said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Ragnhild Kjetland in
Frankfurt at   rkjetland@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Kenneth Wong  in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  